Subject: Discoloration in Ciprofloxacin 500mg tablets - Batch CIP-2406-093

Dear Quality Assurance Team,

We are writing to report a quality issue with a recent shipment of
Ciprofloxacin 500mg tablets, batch number CIP-2406-093, expiry 08/2027.

Three separate patients returned their strips reporting that the tablets had
turned from white to a yellow-brown color. On inspection at our pharmacy the
affected tablets also had a faint sour smell. The blister packs were intact and
had been stored at room temperature as directed.

We have quarantined the remaining stock from this batch and would appreciate
your guidance on returns and any investigation you plan to carry out.

